public interface RoleLevelGoalModel

getEventsToFire

Set<edu.ksu.cis.macr.goal.model.SpecificationEvent> getEventsToFire(edu.ksu.cis.macr.organization.model.SpecificationGoal goal,
                                                                    Object returnValue)
                                                                    throws RoleLevelGoalModel.GoalFailureException
Gets the set of events to fire after completion of the given goal. If the given returnValue is a Boolean, then conditional event firing will occur: If returnValue is true, then only the events that start with "true" are returned. If the returnValue is false, then only the events that start with "false" are returned. If no events named "true" or "false" are found, then all events will be returned

Parameters:
goal - the goal that was just completed
returnValue - the optional return value from the previous goal invocation
Returns:
the set of events that are ready to be fired
Throws:
RoleLevelGoalModel.GoalFailureException - if it was determined, by the given returnValue, that the instance goal failed during execution.
